00:40:16.864 --> 00:40:25.740
I lived in miracles with my mom and dad, and that happened when we were struggling and God provided that way, but it wasn't a way that we wanted to live all the time.

00:40:25.741 --> 00:40:36.879
When you go and you put your boat into motion, go to the place called "there."That's where the provision was.

00:40:36.880 --> 00:40:42.479
And there's so many people that get into weird charismatic flakiness.

00:40:42.480 --> 00:40:48.643
And I'm not dogging the $58 seeds and all the other things that I've heard ministers use in the past.

00:40:48.644 --> 00:40:55.199
Maybe it was anointed at that time and God used it. Is it not the exception but the rule?

00:40:55.200 --> 00:41:06.635
Whatever. Like I said, I get tired of the charismatic flakiness, and there's a lot of it.

00:41:06.636 --> 00:41:22.249
I have seen people get burnt and they walk away discouraged and they leave the church and they don't want anything to do with it because some preacher they think took their money, and they give up tithing, they give up giving.

00:41:22.250 --> 00:41:38.479
And I'm telling you, that's the devil's greatest trick: to make you think that what you gave isn't working because you gave it into bad ground—some 30, some 60, and some 100-fold.

00:41:38.480 --> 00:41:47.358
What's good ground? Quit sowing into bad ground expecting a big harvest.

00:41:47.359 --> 00:41:59.279
You're sowing into sand, bad ground, rocky ground, a lot of you, and you're going, "Why is this ground not producing?"Well, a farmer has enough sense not to keep sowing there.

00:41:59.280 --> 00:42:11.199
But the body of Christ seems to be kind of dumb—excuse it—and they keep sowing there going, "What's wrong with my seed?"Check your soil.

00:42:11.200 --> 00:42:16.808
Where are you sowing? Whatsoever a man sows, that will he also reap.

00:42:16.809 --> 00:42:21.138
But there's a lot of stupid things that people do and they keep sowing into the rocks.

00:42:21.139 --> 00:42:25.311
Sowing into the rocks and they go, "Well, is it going to produce this time?"I'm like, "Well, no.

00:42:25.312 --> 00:42:38.443
If it didn't produce for the last six months, it isn't going to produce now."Check where you're giving and be smart and strategic with your giving.

00:42:38.444 --> 00:42:46.479
Don't give until the Holy Spirit tells you to give. Don't give out of emotion.

00:42:46.480 --> 00:42:52.023
Give being spirit-led. For those that are led by the Spirit of God are the sons and daughters of God.

00:42:52.024 --> 00:43:01.765
And He will lead you into where you're supposed to be giving. Show me, Lord, where I'm getting fed.

00:43:01.766 --> 00:43:09.439
But if you're not getting fed there, and then when you sow there and the cankerworm is eating it up, check where you're at.

00:43:09.440 --> 00:43:21.149
But if you see fruit there and people are getting saved and getting blessed and delivered and healed, then you go, "Well, there's fruit there."So then you have to check your love walk, and people don't want to do that.

00:43:21.150 --> 00:43:34.239
Well, how are you talking to your wife? How are you talking to your husband?

00:43:34.240 --> 00:43:39.189
Because faith works by love, and people don't want to hear that either.

00:43:39.190 --> 00:43:45.079
Well, you've got strife in the house all the time, so you can't always blame it on the ground.

00:43:45.080 --> 00:43:47.039
How are you treating one another? Because faith works by love, and people don't want to hear that.

00:43:47.040 --> 00:43:48.399
Do you know the Bible says that if you treat your wife like trash and you don't respect her, husbands, your prayers will be hindered?

00:43:48.400 --> 00:43:54.879
Well, why are they going to be hindered? Because you aren't treating your wife right.

00:43:54.880 --> 00:43:58.350
You know how many times I go, 'Lord, forgive me,'or 'Diana, you know what?

00:43:58.351 --> 00:44:02.603
I was snappy right there; forgive me, baby. I shouldn't have done that.

00:44:02.604 --> 00:44:10.020
I need my prayers to be heard.'I take it literally. I repent, Father.

00:44:10.021 --> 00:44:15.064
I had a bad attitude right then; I don't want my prayers being hindered.

00:44:15.065 --> 00:44:23.759
Find that scripture, baby, so they can see it with their own eyes.

00:44:23.760 --> 00:44:45.399
'Husbands, honor your wives, or your prayers will be hindered.'I'm not quoting it exactly right, but I know it's in there. 1 Peter 3:7.

00:44:45.400 --> 00:45:10.312
Read 1 Peter 3:7; there's the scripture reference: 'Likewise, ye husbands, dwell with them with understanding, giving honor to your wife as the weaker vessel, and as being heirs together of the grace of life, that your prayers may not be hindered.'So, you want to know why some of your prayers are being hindered?

00:45:10.313 --> 00:45:20.078
How are you treating your wife? That's hard, but a little sugar makes the medicine go down.

00:45:20.079 --> 00:45:27.519
You need to know this. Why are your prayers being hindered? Check your love walk.

00:45:27.520 --> 00:45:30.848
Check how you're treating your wife. Check how you're walking in love.

00:45:30.849 --> 00:45:38.976
Love never fails. How are you doing this? How are you doing that?

00:45:38.977 --> 00:45:45.199
No, listen. You focus on your love walk, and God will take care of the rest.

00:45:45.200 --> 00:45:55.919
Wives, honor your husbands. Proverbs 31—that whole chapter is all about a virtuous woman.

00:45:55.920 --> 00:45:59.752
So ladies, be that. Husbands, be a good husband to your wives.

00:45:59.753 --> 00:46:11.980
There are all kinds of scripture references that you need for how you should be leading your family.

00:46:11.981 --> 00:46:16.270
I don't know why I got off on all that, but I'm talking about the economy.

00:46:16.271 --> 00:46:19.592
The world's economy is different than the spiritual economy.

00:46:19.593 --> 00:46:23.344
We don't abide by the world's economy; we have God's economy.

00:46:23.345 --> 00:46:29.274
And I believe in seedtime and harvest. I believe in tithing. I believe in giving.

00:46:29.275 --> 00:46:38.879
One thing I can tell you, one of the major things I learned when I worked for Mark Crowe—I'll tell his name—he taught me how to tithe.

00:46:38.880 --> 00:46:45.519
He taught me how to tithe, and I worked for him, and he would teach us how to tithe.

00:46:45.520 --> 00:46:57.999
And you know what? It changed my life forever. Changed me forever. Well, 'I don't believe in tithing.'Well, then stay broke.

00:46:58.000 --> 00:47:12.111
I know what the Bible says: 'Give, and it shall be given unto you; good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over.'So, wherever you're getting fed—your pastor, your church, wherever you're plugged in—test the ground.

00:47:12.112 --> 00:47:30.399
Give; bless the kingdom of God. Help them. There are people believing for this end-time harvest, and it's not going to come just by giggles and bubblegum.

00:47:30.400 --> 00:47:42.634
So, I try to help you all as much as I can with the little things because people are freaking out over what I've seen, but I refuse to participate in the world's economic system of debt and the downfall of it.

00:47:42.635 --> 00:47:52.687
Why? Because I live in a heavenly system. And I believe the righteous were never forsaken, nor their seed begging bread.

00:47:52.688 --> 00:47:57.106
If He takes care of the lily of the field, He'll take care of the sparrow of the air.

00:47:57.107 --> 00:48:04.799
He'll take care of Brandon Biggs and his family; how much more are you than them?

00:48:04.800 --> 00:48:18.639
If Jesus said, 'Seek ye first the kingdom, and all these things will be added unto you.'The more you seek Him—if you seek His face—you can have what's in His hand.

00:48:18.640 --> 00:48:30.860
But there are so many people always looking for a lucky 777 lottery winner or whatever the next big fad is—network marketing versus whatever.

00:48:30.861 --> 00:48:40.663
And I'm not knocking network marketing, but it was always pushed around people: 'Sell this, sell this.'Amway and Young Living and this and that, and everybody's selling everything.

00:48:40.664 --> 00:48:45.783
In the body of Christ, network marketing is everything. We had this group over there...

00:48:45.784 --> 00:48:50.540
I remember it. You go into a mega-church like I was at; you had every hall down there.

00:48:50.541 --> 00:48:55.611
We had rooms full of people always talking about network marketing. 'Don't you want to sell this?

00:48:55.612 --> 00:49:03.199
Well, we got this MaxGXL...'I mean, there are so many things people are trying to push.

00:49:03.200 --> 00:49:12.475
'We'll put the man of God at the head of the pyramid so this whole thing will be blessed, and we'll all sow into this and it'll bless the church.'And then, boom!

00:49:12.476 --> 00:49:20.719
And then one thing happened—it was a gas card thing—and everybody was busted by the FBI and they went to prison.

00:49:20.720 --> 00:49:26.021
I believe that was a hoax or something; there are all kinds of things that people had going on over the years.

00:49:26.022 --> 00:49:43.032
And you look at it and go, 'I don't know.'Just my thinking. God help us all get wisdom.

00:49:43.033 --> 00:49:58.715
In all that you do, get wisdom and get some common sense and meditate on His word, and it will change you from the inside out. He's never failed you. He will always take care of you.

00:49:58.716 --> 00:50:06.078
But you have to be listening to that still, small voice inside of you and not listen to all the prophetic nonsense on the internet.

00:50:06.079 --> 00:50:13.358
Listen to the still, small voice on the inside of you. Get in this word, and it will change you from the inside out.

00:50:13.359 --> 00:50:21.424
There's no microwave to it. Quit trying to be lazy. You either do it or you don't.

00:50:21.425 --> 00:50:31.939
But there are no spiritual shortcuts. Do you understand? There are no spiritual shortcuts, ladies and gentlemen.

00:50:31.940 --> 00:50:37.199
It's called a slow cooker. 'Seek Me daily and you will find Me.

00:50:37.200 --> 00:50:42.509
Knock and the door will be opened unto you.'Do you understand?

00:50:42.510 --> 00:50:48.752
It's not a 777 lottery number and a microwave. It doesn't come that way.

00:50:48.753 --> 00:50:55.439
It comes by refining. And refining fire is what changes you.

00:50:55.440 --> 00:50:59.752
That is the sufferings for the greater glory. But people don't want that.

00:50:59.753 --> 00:51:03.712
They say, 'Well, I want a double portion of your anointing.'You know how many people have asked me for that?

00:51:03.713 --> 00:51:07.039
'Now, Brandon, lay hands on me so I can have a double portion.

00:51:07.040 --> 00:51:15.319
I need impartation.'You know what it's called? Knee time. That's impartation: knee time.

00:51:15.320 --> 00:51:30.719
Spend time with Him. There are no shortcuts. 'I want to go to the front of the line.'Well, so did I twenty-five years ago.

00:51:30.720 --> 00:51:46.765
But when you go through the valley, you learn to thirst. All right, let's go.

00:51:46.766 --> 00:51:55.279
That's enough. Oh, Lord, help me. Father, I thank You for the body.

00:51:55.280 --> 00:52:01.313
Who wants to take communion and pray now? But I felt it in my heart to say it.

00:52:01.314 --> 00:52:08.092
You must know the truth. And Jesus wants you to be successful in every area of your life.

00:52:08.093 --> 00:52:12.801
He loves you from Scripture. Look. Here you go. You can just read it.

00:52:12.802 --> 00:52:24.399
And if you want to show it, you can. Now, I want you to see the Sooner.

00:52:24.400 --> 00:52:29.539
We had Japan sign the deal. And now look who's here: South Korea.

00:52:29.540 --> 00:52:34.306
Japan, South Korea. Remember I told you? Sooners. The Sooners.

00:52:34.307 --> 00:52:42.078
Now look what they say right here. Now look at their flag. You see it?

00:52:42.079 --> 00:52:48.476
The Sooners. Boomer Schooner wagon. Remember the Lord said, 'Watch South Korea.

00:52:48.477 --> 00:53:04.065
Watch Japan.'It's happening just like He said. That's neat, Braden.

00:53:04.066 --> 00:53:10.075
You should have told me that earlier. We could have done a dance together. Wow.

00:53:10.076 --> 00:53:12.248
I didn't know until now—until you were doing that—and I started looking.

00:53:12.249 --> 00:53:19.597
I started waking up. I started getting all the stuff from Braden.

00:53:19.598 --> 00:53:29.085
Oh, Jesus, He's so wonderful. The Sooners, huh? Yeah. Isn't Jesus wonderful?

00:53:29.086 --> 00:53:32.283
Accuracy is important, and I don't want to be flaky spiritually.

00:53:32.284 --> 00:53:37.399
Leading all these people like the Lord let us do, we don't want to be flaky.

00:53:37.400 --> 00:53:47.879
And we can miss it. But isn't it nice to see it happening? Oh, what a plan.

00:53:47.880 --> 00:53:50.885
Like Sister Billye always says, 'Oh, what a plan! Oh, what a plan!

00:53:50.886 --> 00:53:54.299
Oh, what a plan! Oh, what a planner, Brandon! Oh, what a plan!

00:53:54.300 --> 00:54:06.354
Oh, what a planner!'Father, we just thank You for it. It is all over Las Vegas.

00:54:06.355 --> 00:54:32.558
What? Yeah, and it's right. Probably nothing though, right? Not financial advice here. Just showing you the news.

00:54:32.559 --> 00:54:40.879
When you pray for something as much as I pray for some things, when you see it in the news, it blesses me.

00:54:40.880 --> 00:54:50.078
I spend hours praying over things the Lord gives me, and you see fruit of your prayers.

00:54:50.079 --> 00:55:10.699
You see it all over the buildings. What's that at? $140. That's interesting.

00:55:10.700 --> 00:55:19.876
It doesn't matter. All right. Let's take communion. Do you have anything else?

00:55:19.877 --> 00:55:23.540
No, go ahead. Oh, you need to see this now. This is important.

00:55:23.541 --> 00:55:30.382
Okay, and then we'll go to pray. This is about the drought the Lord warned us about.

00:55:30.383 --> 00:55:47.199
The worst snowpack in how many years in Colorado? Now listen to this man talk about the snowpack in Denver.

00:55:47.200 --> 00:55:56.558
This is the Antero Reservoir in Colorado. In a few weeks, all of this will be empty.

00:55:56.559 --> 00:56:04.181
Denver Water is draining it, not because something's wrong with the reservoir, but because of the drought, and that means millions of fish could die as well.

00:56:04.182 --> 00:56:10.879
Antero has the highest evaporation rate of any reservoir for Denver Water. Part of that is because it's so shallow.

00:56:10.880 --> 00:56:16.722
But this year's Colorado snowpack was one of the worst in recorded history, and Denver Water needs more water.

00:56:16.723 --> 00:56:24.122
They need to conserve everything that they can. So they're moving the water from here to Cheesman Reservoir where water evaporates slower.

00:56:24.123 --> 00:56:29.451
It'll save enough water for about 15,000 households to have enough water for a year.

00:56:29.452 --> 00:56:36.975
But before that can happen, Colorado Parks and Wildlife is asking as many people as possible to come fish here before the water is gone.

00:56:36.976 --> 00:56:41.919
No bag limits on any species through May 13th. All of these fish are going to die.

00:56:41.920 --> 00:56:46.748
Everything—I mean, even the fish that everybody keeps, they're going to die.

00:56:46.749 --> 00:56:50.490
Whatever people don't come and take, the fish are going to be in the bottom of the lake.

00:56:50.492 --> 00:56:55.199
They're going to be bone-dry skeletons by next year. Travis Sawyer is a fishing guide here.

00:56:55.200 --> 00:56:59.314
He says he's running free trips for people so that they can enjoy the water while it's still here.

00:56:59.315 --> 00:57:05.363
This is one of his favorite places to fish, and he says that people from all over the world fly here for the fish.

00:57:05.365 --> 00:57:14.318
He said, 'We're draining this lake bone dry.'So anything that people don't take is going to be killed.

00:57:14.319 --> 00:57:18.639
The last time that Antero was drained was 2015 for a dam rehabilitation project.

00:57:18.640 --> 00:57:25.358
Before that, it was 2002, also a drought year. It took several years for the fish to become healthy again here after that.

00:57:25.359 --> 00:57:33.718
We've had bad droughts before, but nothing like this one. I'm Mark. I cover Colorado. Follow for more stories like this one.

00:57:33.719 --> 00:57:38.797
So, all those fish—if you like fish and you live in Colorado, that might be a fun day.

00:57:38.798 --> 00:57:43.650
I love fishing. And I tell you what, that would be a fun day for me.

00:57:43.651 --> 00:57:52.991
I'd put all those things in an ice chest and freeze them. There's nothing better than trout to me.

00:57:52.992 --> 00:58:07.913
