00:59:37.920 --> 00:59:43.039
Every breath that proceeds out of you, Father, I want to be close to you.

00:59:43.040 --> 00:59:47.918
Father, I thank you that we hear you and a stranger's voice we will not follow.

00:59:47.919 --> 00:59:55.598
We lift up this body, God, and we're so thankful for your son, Jesus.

00:59:55.599 --> 01:00:02.318
Thank you, Father, that he suffered and died for every single one of us, that we walk in victory.

01:00:02.319 --> 01:00:09.131
Thank you, Lord, that we go from glory to glory. I thank you, Lord, that we are healed and whole and well.

01:00:09.132 --> 01:00:15.475
We don't have to have sickness and disease in our bodies anymore because by your stripes, we're healed.

01:00:15.476 --> 01:00:22.326
We take this body in the name of Jesus and we give you all the glory, honor, and praise for what you did for us.

01:00:22.327 --> 01:00:48.596
Amen. We apply the blood of Jesus over us and we thank you, Father, that it never loses its power.

01:00:48.597 --> 01:00:56.496
It covers us from the top of our head to the soles of our feet, uninterrupted and unhindered by any satanic or demonic force.

01:00:56.497 --> 01:01:38.430
We rebuke the devil in the name of Jesus. Amen. Over our children, our wives, and our finances.

01:01:38.431 --> 01:02:58.239
Father, open the eyes of our heart. I want to see you high and lifted up, shining in the light of your glory.

01:02:58.240 --> 01:03:32.719
Pour out your power and love as we sing holy, holy, holy. I want to see you.

01:03:32.720 --> 01:04:27.287
Lord, there are so many people here tonight that are thirsty.

01:04:27.288 --> 01:04:49.598
We lift up our cup before you and say, 'Fill it.'Come and quench this thirsting of our soul.

